claim.claim-text:
A stent (1) formed into a generally or substantially tubular body with annular units composed of a plurality of cells and being expandable radially outward from inside of the tubular body,
wherein the plurality of the cells (6) are connected vertically and so arranged as to surround the central axis (C1) of the stent (1) which forms the tubular body and thereby forming the annular units (4);
wherein the plurality of said annular units (4) are disposed in the axial direction of said stent (1), and said adjacent annular units (4) are connected at least at one portion by a connecting part (5);
wherein said connecting part (5) is formed of a bent portion (8) having at least two or more arcs and an approximately or substantially straight line portion (7) continuing to the bent portion (8), the ends of said bent portion (8) are respectively connected to the left portion and the right portion of said cells (6) forming adjacent annular units (1) respectively;
characterized in that: (A) each of said cells being composed of two struts, one strut being composed of an approximately or substantially straight line portion (SLP-Strut) and the other strut being composed of a curved line portion (CLP-strut), and one strut being disposed in the axial direction thus comprising a base strut (BS-strut), and the other strut being disposed at an acute angle (X) with respect to the axial direction thus comprising a bending strut (BN-strut), and,
wherein;
each of said cells (6) has a center line (C2) in the axial direction of the stent (1) and is formed of two struts by connecting (i) the approximately or substantially straight line portion (11) (SLP-Strut) disposed almost horizontally to the center line (C2) or axial direction and, (ii) the curved line portion (13)(CLP-strut) disposed at an acute angle (X) with respect to the center line (C2) or the axial direction through a bent portion (12),
wherein an approximately or substantially straight line portion (15) forming a part of said curved line portion (13) (CLP-strut) and being adjacent to said bent portion (12) is connected to the approximately or substantially straight line portion (11) (SLP-Strut) disposed almost horizontally to the center line (C2) in the axial direction of the stent through said bent portion (12), and thereby
said cells (6) are being formed to be vertically asymmetrical to the center line (C2) when divided vertically by the center line (C2) in the axial direction of the stent (1), thereby compression of the stent is carried out while said SLP-strut comprising the base strut (BS-Strut) maintaining the axial direction, and said CLP-Strut comprising the bending strut (BN-Strut) being bent toward the base strut (BS-Strut),
and (B) said stent (1) being expandable to at least diameter (ϕ) 2.5 mm, wherein the stent (1) is being formed in a manner that the angle (θ) formed between said approximately or substantially straight line portion (15) adjacent to said bent portion (12) and said approximately or substantially straight line portion (11) (SLP-Strut) is 30°-140° after expansion when the diameter (ϕ) of said annular body is expanded to 2.5 mm.
